# Customer Churn MLOps Pipeline

# Project Overview
This project implements an end-to-end MLOps pipeline for customer churn prediction. The main goal is to design a system that can handle data ingestion, preprocessing, model training, deployment, and monitoring in a structured and reproducible way.
The system predicts whether a customer is likely to churn based on input features.A lightweight Streamlit frontend is also included to allow interactive user predictions.


# Pipeline Structure
The pipeline consists of the following components:

1. Data Ingestion  
Historical data is collected from an external source and stored locally. New data is added to simulate live incoming data. Each ingestion step is logged to track updates.

2. Preprocessing  
The data is cleaned by handling missing values, converting data types, and encoding categorical variables. Feature engineering is also applied where necessary.

3. Model Training  
A machine learning model is trained using the processed dataset. The trained model is saved as an artifact for reuse.

4. Deployment  
A FastAPI application is used to serve the trained model. The API accepts input data and returns predictions.

5. Monitoring  
Prediction logs are stored to track system behavior. Data ingestion is also logged to monitor data updates over time.


# Project Structure
customer-churn-mlops
├── app/            # FastAPI application
├── src/            # pipeline scripts (ingestion, preprocessing, training)
├── data/           # datasets
├── artifacts/      # model, logs, metrics
├── frontend.py     # Streamlit frontend
├── Dockerfile      # container setup


# How to Run (without Docker)
Step 1: Install dependencies  
pip install -r requirements.txt  

Step 2: Run the API  
uvicorn app.main:app --reload  

Step 3: Open browser  
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs  

Step 4: Run Streamlit frontend
streamlit run frontend.py

Step 5: Frontend can be accessed locally via:
http://localhost:8501

# How to Run with Docker
Step 1: Build Docker image  
docker build -t churn-app .  

Step 2: Run container  
docker run -p 8000:8000 churn-app  

Step 3: Open  
http://localhost:8000/docs  


# API Usage
Use the /predict endpoint.
